**Abstract:**
A major essay dated April 14, 1992, titled "Theodicy and 'Meta-physics'," comparing the relationship between physics and philosophy of physics to that between religion and philosophy of religion. The document argues that confusing these yields enormous mistakes, as Pascal noted in claiming the God of philosophers is not the God of Jesus-Christ. It traces the historical transformation from theology as practical reflection (intra-communitary practices responding to community needs) to theology as specialized academic discipline, arguing that early Christian theological practices were fundamentally practical, oriented toward enhancing Christian life rather than satisfying intellectual curiosity.

**AI Recommendation:** Important essay on the professionalization of theology and the shift from practical to theoretical orientation; develops the distinction between religion and philosophy of religion.

